task.summary: Default task
Added changes and removed the money and transaction classes, running back on basics for now
Ok trying to ensure that the integration with the CI server is working. Here is hoping
Implemented the basis of auctions and and improved the Bank file, bit by bit coming together.

Ok made changes to incorporate the adjustment of rules, created the classes for the GUI. Also need to find an elegant way to make Bank a singleton, going to have tomorrow off, need a rest. But Hopefully have all the basic rules done and the the basis of a GUI by the end of next week. I need to improve my tests, they are not rigorous enough.

Made bank singleton also added an abstract class called ownable, which allows for a better inheritence of classes and allows for better written bank class, the bank is almost completed, but still need to work at it.
Made minor changes to the bank class and tests, also written new tests and new class rules. Seems the transactions have been implemented now to move onto the implementing the basis of all the rules.
Completed the utility rules, and tested the extensibility, need to test the full workings of the utility board class, but that will be soon
Minor mistake on the CSV file to do with income tax, nothing major.
Implemented station rules and tested
Implemented Tax rules and tested
Break in the build due to the tests landing on the tax board, from what I can tell I need to work out a sensible way of writing the player tests as a lot of mocking and stubbing is required

Started to look into the bankruptcy checks, seems to be working, need to run more tests. Player logic really needs to be developed, but I also need to ensure all the board is tested as currently it is not.
Finished the board logic, it really needs to be tested though, but at 2am , I think I am done for the night. Thank you and Good NIGHT!
Fixed the failed build hopefully all works

Implmented bankruptcy checks and what to do if the user is bankrupt, still need to work out the logic for the player on how to deal with not having enough money but being able to sell all their items.
Ok refactored some code, improved the player dice roll, and refractored changes throughout
Ok finished the rules and unit tested them, Now moving onto the players logic. This may take a while
Started to implement the methods of the player logic and test them, this will take time, but it is building slowly

Huge changes made to the framework of the code, moving away from java, using it mostly as a top layer and structure, the core of the logic will be written in LUA, this will allow for changes to be made on the program during runtime, and allows for limitless possibilities to incorporate new rules. Currently two weeks behind schedule. need to put the hours in.
Minor changes to the tests as the paths where absolute and should be relative, this fix should allow for the correct integration within the CI server
Sellling Rules implemented in lua
Auction Rules implemented and tested in Lua
Station rules Implemented and tested in java.
Tax Rules Implemented and tested in lua
Utility Rules implemented and tested in Lua
